==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silicic
<hw>Si*lic"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>silex</ets>, <ets>silicis</ets>, a flint: cf. F.
<ets>silicique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to,
derived from, or resembling, silica; specifically, designating compounds
of silicon; <as>as, <ex>silicic</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silicic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
amorphous gelatinous substance, <chform>Si(HO)4</chform>, very unstable
and easily dried to silica, but forming many stable salts; -- called
also <altname>orthosilicic acid</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>normal
silicic acid</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicicalcareous</ent>⟦br⟧
